review:
Stealth action puzzler with so much depth in its mechanics and maps, I'm still finding new parts of the game 3+years since the "first" HITMAN.  It's one of the few games I consistently come back to: 
[list]
[*]placing a headshot on targets with the silenced pistols is always rewarding;
[*]the AI reactions are satisfying;
[*]trying a new approach or a new record on a speedrun stimulates the brain muscles without overwhelming;
[*]there's so many little details and hidden approaches in a single mission that can keep you discovering more; and
[*]there's new content from users and the developer (via DLC).
[/list]

HITMAN™ 2 gets it right again!
if you like any Hitman game you will love this one. If only it was longer :)
Amyway, all thumbs up for this one!
